petQuotes.quote: Quite lackluster was thine food.
Thou food was of upmost disgust. Revenge will be mine!
Time waits for no man. Feedth me now!
Why doth feed me so much? I shall not transform into Edward the blowfish
You hath brought mere bore out of me
Thee crickets are as fat as butter
I would give all my Frogdom for a pot of ale
Have you heardth of diet Croak? *whispers* Thy heard it's to die for
Oy jester, why doth thou drive beetles when they fly?
Thy don't feel like hopping today. Carry me
Thy has gold since
Thy do love nothing in the world so well as you: is not that strange?
What a majestic day!
The world is thine oyster!
What should thou do thee present day
We meeteth again
True love lies beneath the ribs. The belly!
Sound the bell jester! We shall have a ball
Thou is my truest jester. Salute
I am fill'd with pangs of hunger
This weather is reminiscent of the darks days of Froglaland
Let the frogdom know the King calls for a day of rest. Being a ruler is tiresome
Well all's well that ends well
Thou seen better days.
Thy feelth thee most sick
